## Decisions
- **No `<RosterGrid>` extraction.** Inlined the grid in `subject-register-editor`
  rather than refactoring slice 7's `register-editor` to share one. That editor is
  manually-verified, **test-unguarded** UI; the regression risk of refactoring it
  outweighs the DRY win for one more consumer. The cp1 "2-consumers → extract"
  threshold doesn't carry when one consumer is already shipped + unguarded. Only
  `status-meta` (pure styling) is shared.
- **Flag read split:** the sidebar + the manager scope use `getSchoolMe` (any
  authed role); the teacher scope uses the flag riding on `/teacher-scope/me`.
  Both resolve the same `School.subjectAttendanceEnabled`.
- **Owner/admin reach the subject surface** at `/teacher/attendance/subject`
  (RequireAuth only, same as slice 7), seeing every subject + arm.

