## Two bugs caught in the S2 manual walk (fixed, web-only)
1. **Privilege-surface: teacher could load the (admin) shell.** `(admin)/layout`
   was `RequireAuth` (authed-only), so a teacher reached `/settings/*` and saw
   the admin sidebar (the PATCH was still server-gated, but the surface was
   wrong). Fix: `RequireAuth` gained an optional `roles` prop; the (admin) layout
   now passes `["owner","admin"]` and bounces teachers to `/teacher/dashboard`.
   The (teacher) layout stays role-open (owner/admin may view teacher pages).
   Follow-up: the redirect first targeted `/teacher` (no index page → 404); the
   canonical landing is `/teacher/dashboard`. Fixed there AND in the two
   subject-page flag-gate redirects (same latent `/teacher` 404).
2. **Sidebar flag read.** The "Subject attendance" entry read the flag via
   `getSchoolMe`. Although `/schools/me` is in fact open to any authed role (so
   this wasn't a 403), the plan-first decision was to read it from
   `/teacher-scope/me` so the teacher portal never depends on a school-settings
   read. Switched the sidebar to `getMyScope().subjectAttendanceEnabled`. (The
   "missing entry" symptom was really bug 1 — the teacher was looking at the
   admin sidebar.) Verified the live dev flag is `true` and `/teacher-scope/me`
   carries it.

## Bug caught in S3 — infinite register re-fetch loop (subject page only)
The subject register page passed an **inline arrow** `onLoaded={({…}) =>
setLastMarkedAt(stamp)}`. The editor's `load` useCallback lists `onLoaded` in
its deps, so a new arrow every render recreated `load` → `useEffect([load])`
refired → `load()` set a fresh `Date` into the lifted stamp → re-render → new
arrow → loop (~6.3k requests in 5 min). The slice-7 **daily** page does NOT have
this — it already memoised `handleLoaded` with `useCallback([])`. Fix: mirror
that — memoise `handleLoaded` in the subject page and pass it instead of the
inline arrow. Loop gone; the fetch effect fires once per
(subject, arm, date, period) change. (The subject **summary** page has no
`onLoaded` and primitive-only `load` deps — not affected.)

