## WS2 — Phase 2 audit-coverage
Extended `apps/api/src/__tests__/audit-coverage.spec.ts` with a "Phase 2 audit
coverage" describe block mirroring the Phase 1 one: every Phase 2 mutation writes
an audit row with the expected **action + actor (userId) + metadata-shape**
(required keys present, not exact values). Two schools — a "config" school
(grading + school.update; freely mutates the seeded scheme since no scores → not
frozen) and a "pipeline" school (assessment → report-card → attendance, sharing a
real BullMQ queue + filesystem storage like the workflow specs). 18 actions
covered: grading-scheme.update, grading-component.create/update/delete,
grade-boundary.update, assessment-score.create/update, assessment.sign-off,
assessment.aggregate, report-card.build/comment(×2)/form-review/approve/release/
reopen/render-batch, attendance.mark, subject-attendance.mark, school.update.

Fixture notes: a **weight-0** grading component keeps Σ=100 so create + delete
both validate; report cards must be **built, commented, then column-signed-off
(cascade → SUBJECT_REVIEWED)** before form-review (it 409s otherwise — DRAFT
isn't enough).

### TWO FINDINGS (surfaced + reported back; rulings 2026-06-10)
1. **Render IS audited.** The plan assumed `POST /report-cards/arm/render` writes
   no audit row ("intentional absence"). It does: `enqueueArmRender` writes
   **`report-card.render-batch`** and the render worker writes
   **`report-card.render`** per card. The plan-first Q8 assumption was wrong; the
   spec asserts the actual behavior. (Ruling 2026-06-10: keep as-is — auditing is
   appropriate for PDF-debug forensics.)
2. **`approve` audit action diverges from its permission name.** The approve
   transition writes audit action **`report-card.approve`** while its
   `@Permissions` key + the spec say **`report-card.principal-approve`**. The spec
   asserts the ACTUAL `report-card.approve` (true regression guard) with a comment
   flagging the divergence. Surfaced for a ruling. (Ruling 2026-06-10: RENAME to
   `report-card.principal-approve` — see the 2026-06-10 entry.)

No coverage GAPS found — every state-changing Phase 2 endpoint writes an audit row.

## WS4 — `/schools/me` tighten
`GET /schools/me` now asserts owner/admin in the service (`findMe` →
`assertUserActiveAndHasOneOf(["owner","admin"])`), closing the slice-8-cp2
finding (any authed user could read school config). **Service-level role
assertion, not `@Permissions("school.read")`:** the latter would force
`PermissionsGuard` onto the whole Phase-0 schools controller incl. the onboarding
handler (no clean permission) — that retrofit stays deferred with the rest of
Phase 0. Pre-tighten grep confirmed **no teacher path calls `/schools/me`**:
the admin settings page + the manager (owner/admin) branch of
`use-subject-attendance-scope` are the only callers; teachers read the school
name from `/auth/me` and the subject flag from `/teacher-scope/me`. Tests added:
admin reads OK, teacher → 403.

